SIMPLE: chaser
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chaser
<hw>Chas"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who or
that which chases; a pursuer; a driver; a hunter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Same as <er>Chase gun</er>, esp.
in terms <stype>bow chaser</stype> and <stype>stern chaser</stype>. See
under <er>Bow</er>, <er>Stern</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chaser</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Chaser
<hw>Chas"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who chases or
engraves. See 5th <er>Chase</er>, and <er>Enchase</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>A tool with several points, used
for cutting or finishing screw threads, either external or internal, on
work revolving in a lathe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chasible</ent>⟦br⟧
